  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Assistance to Displaced Populations in Chad: Displacement Tracking and Non-Food Items</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed action aims to build on the current Displacement Tracking Matrix (DTM) exercise to produce precise data and information to best inform humanitarian interventions carried out by governmental and humanitarian partners. IOM proposes to build up its capacity to be able to respond to the information needs, as expressed in the Humanitarian Response Plan (HRP) and by the different cluster partners, by reinforcing its Displacement Tracking Matrix and extending it to the south. In addition to this, the proposed action will provide direct assistance to the most vulnerable Internally Displaced Population (IDP) households identified, through the provision of emergency Non-Food Items(NFI) assistance.</narrative>
  </description>
